We have, $$\int_0^{2\pi } {{{\sin }^5}\left( {{x \over 4}} \right)dx} $$<br><br>Let $${x \over 4} = t \Rightarrow dx = 4dt$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $$\int_0^{\pi /2} {{{\sin }^5}t.4dt = 4\int_0^{\pi /2} {{{\sin }^5}t\,dt} } $$<br><br>By Walli's formula,<br><br>$$\int_0^{\pi /2} {{{\sin }^n}dx = \int_0^{\pi /2} {{{\cos }^n}x\,dx} } $$<br><br>$$ = \left[ \matrix{
  {{n - 1} \over n}.{{n - 3} \over {n - 2}}.{{n - 5} \over {n - 4}}...{2 \over 3},\,n\,is\,odd \hfill \cr 
  {{n - 1} \over n}.{{n - 3} \over {n - 2}}.{{n - 5} \over {n - 4}}...{3 \over 4}.{1 \over 2}.{\pi  \over 2},\,when\,n\,is\,even \hfill \cr}  \right.$$<br><br>$$ = 4.{{4.2} \over {5.3}} = {{32} \over {15}}$$

